{
  "stem": "24111.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, perhaps in the best way, it would be $10.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I forgot to mention, the soup kitchen produced an one-pot meal, which was a little bit thicker soup.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't want to-- I don't want that you think that was a-- a dinner served.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was just a one-pot meal.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And also, you got a slice of bread.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The bread was very restrictive.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I believe it was 100 gram a day per-- per person.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So you try to save part of the bread for the morning, breakfast, or for the evening, because when you ate it-- when you ate it, it was all you had.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I remember my mother tried to doctor up the meal with a little bit-- whatever she-- she could get otherwise too.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I remember also that from that time on, I believe for years to come, I was always hungry.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was my growing years, and I needed perhaps more.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were not allowed to buy at all.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So what we did?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We bartered.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We bartered with other Jews.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was an giving-- giving and take.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My free time-- I forgot to tell you too that we worked six days, not like here 40 hours.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We worked perhaps 10 hours a day, 6 days a week.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we had only the Sunday free.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the Sundays I always spent in the JUL, in the--",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--group of Aron Menczer.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I met a lot of [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Jews in my age group, girls and boys.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that was actually the happiest times I had, with them for a few hours, because when I had to go home, it was depressing.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
